        <h1>Finsbury Park bus station closure - Monday 22 November until Friday 10 December</h1>
        <div class="content-page-press-release">
        15 November 2010
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="main-and-aside r">
    <div class="main" role="main">

    <div class="article-teaser">
        From Monday 22 November, Finsbury Park bus station at Station Place will be closed for refurbishment works. The bus station will close at 07:00, reopening at 16:00 on Friday 10 December.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<p>The following routes will be affected by the closure: 19, 106, 153, 236, and N19. </p>
<p>Routes 19, 106, 236, and N19 towards Finsbury Park will be diverted from St Thomas's Road via Seven Sisters Road and Isledon Road (passengers to alight at stop T). </p>
<p>Routes 19, 106, 236, and N19 from Finsbury Park will be diverted from the stand at Coleridge Road via Seven Sisters Road, Station Road and Blackstock Road. </p>
<p>The nearest bus stop for passengers is stop N in Blackstock Road.<br>&nbsp;<br>Route 153 towards Finsbury Park will be diverted via Isledon Road to a temporary stop (passengers to alight at stop X). </p>
<p>Route 153 from Finsbury Park will be diverted from Isledon Road to its normal line of route. </p>
<p>The nearest bus stop for passengers is stop T on Isledon Road. </p>
<p>Details of diversions and stopping arrangements during this closure will be available at local bus stops, around the bus station and on <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk">Transport for London's&nbsp;website</a>. </p>
<p>Bus station staff will also be available to advise passengers of where to catch their bus. </p>
<p>

     

        
        
        
